WHO   — ATARI JAGUAR — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Atari's last console was marketed as the first '64-bit' system, but inside was a tangle of chips that almost nobody could program well: two powerful custom processors ('Tom' and 'Jerry') alongside an old 68000 that developers leaned on out of habit — strangling the very power Atari was advertising.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
